{
  "stem": "21482.4",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I think that we probably went there in 1943, towards the-- maybe in December, November, December.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then we stayed there until 1944 in, in August, late August.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then we came to him and sent back to Plaszow because the camp was being liquidated.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And Oskar Schindler said he was going to move his camp to the factory to bring it to Czechoslovakia, and he was going to take us.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He again, we had alll-- he assembled us all in a courtyard.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And he told us the factory is going to be moved, Plaszow is being liquidated.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We are going to be sent back to Plaszow, and then we're going to come to Czechoslovakia.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "In order to make sure that we would all come, we were tattooed.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We were tattooed with KL, for Konzentration Lager.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And it was done by the Jewish doctors in the camps.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So, you know, they didn't do that deep, and it disappeared.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "There's hardly just, just a few little spots on my skin are left.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And so we were sent back to Plaszow at that time.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "There was hardly anybody left because Plaszow was liquidated in August.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "The men and the women who are working in Plaszow were working in the different workshops.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "They were all sent-- the men were sent to Mauthausen, to Gross-Rosen, to Mauthausen, and the woman were sent to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "The few people that were left-- Amon Goth was not there anymore.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "The few people that were left, we work in a warehouse packing for Germany in boxes, cartons, in suitcase, in trucks gold, silver, brass, paintings, clothing, furs.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And they would ship everything that they plundered.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Everything the Germans stole, they brought it to Plaszow and we were packing it.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
